704899f-a.title: Brooklyn: Hewes Street - Kent Avenue
704899f-a.text:
Hewes Street, at the S.E. corner of Kent Ave. The long view of the
building is on Hewes Street. In the foreground, is Classon Ave., intersect-
ing with Hewes Street and Kent Ave.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

704898f-a.title: Brooklyn: Hewes Street - Kent Avenue
704898f-a.text:
Hewes Street, south side, west from Kent Ave. A view of D. Appleton's
old plant. He founded the publishing house bearing his name in 1825.
April 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
